{
  "narration": "As the sounds of the command post buzz around you, Elen turns, her eyes sharpened by the gravity of your question. She crosses her arms and stands beside the battered map table, inviting you and Kira closer. \"To truly bolster our defenses before the Crow's Hand strikes, we'll need more than just hope and sharp eyes.\"\n\nShe gestures to the table, where pins mark the approaches to the outpost. \"First, reinforcing the silver bell network is vital. Any silence along the wires must be checked--run a sweep of every post, especially those near the woods edge. Second, we could use more barricades and cover here in the main yard. Spare timber, overturned wagons, anything sturdy. Third, the supply depot has old hunting traps and caltrops. If we scatter some in likely approach routes, we might slow or wound the bandits before they reach us.\"\n\nElen's expression softens just a touch. \"And, well, your healing and leadership--should things turn bloody. If you have spells or tools to bolster our rangers, prepare them now.\"\n\nKira chimes in, slinging her bow over her shoulder. \"I'll sweep the bell posts and the north fence line. Eirik, if you help set the traps or check the barricades, we can cover more ground. Or you could talk to the supply clerks and see what extra gear they're hiding.\"\n\nElen nods in agreement. \"It's your call, Eirik. Every minute counts. Where do you want to focus your efforts?\"",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 4
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Elen nods at your decision. \"A smart move, Eirik. If the Crow's Hand left anything behind at the waystations, it might be the edge we need. Anything that tells us more about their numbers, tactics, or timing could help us prepare.\"\n\nKira gives you a quick salute, her eyes glinting. \"I'll grab my cloak and meet you at the gate. The trail between here and the Forgotten Waystation should still be fresh from our last search. With luck, we might spot something we missed.\"\n\nThe rangers at the post tighten their patrols and begin reinforcing the barricades as you and Kira set out, boots crunching over the dew-soaked earth. The tension of the outpost fades behind you, replaced by the quiet focus of experienced scouts returning to the field. The path ahead is clear: first to Trader's Rest, then onward to the ruins of the Forgotten Waystation, where the frost and tangled underbrush might still hide secrets left by fleeing bandits or saboteurs.\n\nThe air is crisp, the morning sun breaking through high clouds as you and Kira make your way west, eyes keen for any sign of trouble or clues. As you approach the crossroads leading to Trader's Rest, Kira murmurs, \"Keep your eyes peeled, Eirik. If Rusk passed this way, he may have left a trail--or a trap.\"\n\nYou arrive at Trader's Rest, the clearing quiet but watchful, the silver bell post glinting faintly in the daylight. Where will you begin your search: the crates, the bell post, or the merchant encampment?",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "transitionLocation",
      "parameters": {
        "newLocation": "RO03"
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 10
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "The clearing at Trader's Rest is eerily calm under the brightening midday sun. You and Kira scan the ground, searching for any sign of a trail left by Rusk or the Crow's Hand saboteur. The grass around the battered crates is scuffed, and you notice a few fresh bootprints and a faint drag mark snaking westward toward the Forgotten Waystation.\n\nKira crouches, examining the ground. \"Looks like something--or someone--was dragged this way. The mud's still soft. If we hurry, we might catch up to whoever passed through.\"\n\nShe gives you a determined nod. \"Ready to press on, Eirik? If we're lucky, we might find more clues at the old ruins. Just keep your eyes open--no telling if they left traps or sentries behind.\"\n\nAs you prepare to follow the trail toward the Forgotten Waystation, the packed dirt path narrows, framed by tangled shrubbery and frostbitten roots. The forest is still, but the sense of being watched lingers at the edge of your awareness.\n\nWill you take point and lead the way, or let Kira scout ahead? Either way, a careful eye could reveal danger--or a clue--before you reach the next stop on the saboteur's path.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "transitionLocation",
      "parameters": {
        "newLocation": "RO05"
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 10
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "You and Kira pause just inside the vine-choked boundary of the Forgotten Waystation. The ruins stand silent, sunlight filtering through broken timbers and mossy stone, casting wavering shadows across the trampled grass. Kira slips her bow from her shoulder and crouches low, her sharp eyes scanning the ground for clues. \"All right, Eirik, keep an eye on the treeline. If Rusk or the Crow's Hand left anything, I'll find it.\"\n\nYou steady your mace and shield, eyes sweeping the tangled outskirts and the collapsed wall. The silence is pierced only by the distant call of a jay and the soft crunch of Kira's boots as she moves among the remnants of battered crates and scattered debris.\n\nKira kneels by a patch of disturbed earth, brushing aside fallen leaves. \"Tracks are recent. Two, maybe three people, one dragging something heavy. Looks like they doubled back after the sabotage at Trader's Rest... and here--see this scuffed mark? Could be from a boot with a missing heel.\"\n\nShe glances back, voice low. \"I'll keep following these. If you want to check the old lockbox or the collapsed storage behind the crates, we might get lucky. Just call out if you spot anything odd.\"\n\nThe air feels tense with expectation. Eirik, do you want to investigate the lockbox, the collapsed wall, or circle the perimeter for threats? If you choose to investigate, please make an Investigation or Perception check and let me know your roll.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 5
      }
    }
  ]
}
